Brogan is part of the [[Ontario, Oregon|Ontario]], OR&ndash;[[Idaho|ID]] [[Ontario micropolitan area|Micropolitan Statistical Area]]. At the [[2010 United States census|2010 census]], the population was 90 (47 female and 43 male). The median age was 50.5 years. There were 41 households, five of which included children under age 18.<ref name=census>{{cite web|url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US4108600|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200212145258/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US4108600|url-status=dead|archive-date=February 12, 2020|title=2010 Demographic Profile Data: Brogan CDP, Oregon|work=American FactFinder|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|accessdate=July 26, 2014}}</ref>

As of the 2020 census, there were 97 people, 58 housing units, and 16 families in the CDP. There were 88 [[White Americans|White]] people, 6 people from some other race, and 3 people from two or more races. 9 people were [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/profile?g=160XX00US4108600 |access-date=2023-05-23 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

The ancestry in Brogan was 61% [[Irish Americans|Irish]], and 39% [[Italian Americans|Italian]].<ref name=":0" />

The median age was 51.9 years old. 48.8% of the population were older than 65, with 24.4% between the ages of 65 and 74, 9.8% between the ages of 75 and 84, and 14.6% older than 85 years old.<ref name=":0" />

0.0% of the population was in poverty, and the median income was not recorded.<ref name=":0" />

